					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jonnyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(248389); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=248389&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182906" alt="JonnyD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=248389)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jonnyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(248389); return false;" >JonnyD</a></span> <span class="odate time_1239495757 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Apr 2009 00:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-446318">
									

<p>I've had a bit of a hiatus since my first 3 SCP creations, but I found some spare time and had an idea rattling round my head.</p>
<p>I figured that this would be a good deterrent against tomb robbers. Try and steal it and it'll subject you to an eternity of agony. If someone try's to take it off you, you die and they end up trapped in agony. No matter how many times you kill the person, they just grow back.</p>
<p>I guess the only way out is to destroy the statue itself, but I think the Foundation would find an endless supply of blood and organs too good to pass up. Obviously they could practically get that from the class D's anyway, but this way they can make copies of rare blood and organs.</p>
<p>And I know that a Foundation ethics committee might sound like an oxymoron, but since the site is about horror, what job could be more horrible than trying to answer the ethical questions that Foundation activities raise.</p>

							</div>

								
