														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-446431">
									

<p>I've made the change you suggested. I'm new to the threat diamond and I wasn't sure if it warranted a level 4. It's not dangerous to be around or near or even to touch so long as you don't let it touch your bare skin, and it's certainly not <em>actively</em> trying to kill anyone. But reading over the descriptions again, I think you're right, that it does kill you dead (eventually), so it should be a class 4.</p>
<p>I hadn't thought of experiments with painkillers as opposed to sedatives. To be honest the exact nature of what SCP-596 inflicts upon the subjects that makes then scream for the rest of their lives is perhaps the only mysterious element. I guess I see the foundation as being more interested in what they can get out of it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
